headline: CSX lost out on $1 million a day in Q1 revenue amid hurricane, tunnel work
summary: Rebuilding after hurricane damage and rerouting around a Baltimore tunnel project cost CSX a million dollars a day in lost revenue in the first quarter, a company executive told an investor conference. The post CSX lost out on $1 million a day in Q1 revenue amid hurricane, tunnel work appeared first on FreightWaves.
